com.github.i49.hibiscus.schema

Interface JsonType

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ArrayType, AtomicType, BooleanType, CompositeType, IntegerType, NullType, NumberType, ObjectType, StringType

    public interface JsonType
    A base type of all built-in types available in schema definitions. These built-in types include array, boolean, integer, number, null, object and string.

    • Method Summary

      • validateInstance

        default void validateInstance(JsonValue value,
                              List<Problem> problems)
        Validates a value of this type in JSON document and reports problems if detected. This method is for internal use only and only JsonValidator implementations are allowed to call this method directly.
        Parameters:
        value - the value in JSON document. Cannot be null.
        problems - the list to which detected problems to be added. Cannot be null.
